Author: sonorie
Text: Yes and no? It's weird. I have gotten really good at guessing weights, but at the same time I need everyone to weigh more than me. So people are usually at or heavier than the number my brain expects, but lighter than the number my heart expects.    I've never thought about it like that though. I could totally be looking at this as an opportunity to get a more realistic take on things. There's probably a healthy lesson to learn here!

Author: TheBonesRTheirMoney
Text: Are most people heavier than you expected? Or do you think you have a more realistic view of body volume & weight after seeing so much data?
